---
By: Fred Van Amburgh
Locus:
  Page: 160
  Verse: 16
Tags:
  - Fault
---
It requires no thought, no consideration, no character, no talent to be a
fault-finder. ...It is much easier to find fault then to find ways to help.
...How easy to be critical and how hard to be correct. How easy to find
fault with others and how hard to mend our own ways.
